* 9.Universidad de Chile     18  5  1 12  37-45  11
*10.Badminton      17  3  3 11  33-49   9
*
*NB: The two missing matches were never played and nobody officially knows why.  It is said that Colo Colo argued that they were about  to start some international matches and they didn't have enough time. Secretly, they might have been afraid of losing their last match to Badminton and thereby their unbeaten status, as they considered Badminton their "bête noire". In 1937, they had almost lost to Badminton in the final round that season, which also then would have been their first loss in the championship that year. 


